# Docker Day 2 Commands – Docker Images, Docker Hub & CI/CD

## Build a Docker Image

```bash
docker build -t hello-docker .
```

Builds a Docker image from the Dockerfile in the current directory.

---

## Build an Image with a Specific Tag

```bash
docker build -t hello-docker:v1 .
```

Creates an image with the specified version tag.

---

## List Docker Images

```bash
docker images
```

Displays all Docker images available on the local machine.

---

## Inspect an Image

```bash
docker image inspect hello-docker
```

Displays detailed information about a Docker image.

---

## View Image History (Layers)

```bash
docker history hello-docker
```

Shows the image layers created during the build process.

---

## Run a Docker Image

```bash
docker run hello-docker
```

Creates and starts a container from the image.

---

## Run a Container in Detached Mode

```bash
docker run -d hello-docker
```

Runs the container in the background.

---

## Map Host Port to Container Port

```bash
docker run -p 5001:5000 python-hello-world
```

Maps port **5001** on the host to port **5000** inside the container.

---

## Run a Container with a Custom Name

```bash
docker run --name my-container hello-docker
```

Starts a container with a user-defined name.

---

## View Running Containers

```bash
docker ps
```

Displays only running containers.

---

## View All Containers

```bash
docker ps -a
```

Displays both running and stopped containers.

---

## View Container Logs

```bash
docker logs <container_id>
```

Displays the logs generated by a container.

---

## Stop a Running Container

```bash
docker stop <container_id>
```

Stops a running container gracefully.

---

## Remove a Container

```bash
docker rm <container_id>
```

Deletes a stopped container.

---

## Remove All Stopped Containers

```bash
docker container prune
```

Removes all stopped containers from the system.

---

## Login to Docker Hub

```bash
docker login
```

Authenticates with your Docker Hub account.

---

## Tag an Image for Docker Hub

```bash
docker tag hello-docker <dockerhub-username>/hello-docker
```

Prepares the image for uploading to Docker Hub.

---

## Push an Image to Docker Hub

```bash
docker push <dockerhub-username>/hello-docker
```

Uploads the Docker image to Docker Hub.

---

## Pull an Image from Docker Hub

```bash
docker pull <dockerhub-username>/hello-docker
```

Downloads a Docker image from Docker Hub.

---

## Remove an Image

```bash
docker rmi hello-docker
```

Deletes a Docker image from the local machine.

---

## Remove Unused Images

```bash
docker image prune
```

Removes dangling (unused) Docker images.

---

## Remove Unused Docker Resources

```bash
docker system prune
```

Removes stopped containers, unused networks, dangling images, and build cache.

---

## Docker Image Workflow

```text
Write Application
        ↓
Create Dockerfile
        ↓
docker build
        ↓
Docker Image
        ↓
docker run
        ↓
Docker Container
        ↓
docker tag
        ↓
docker push
        ↓
Docker Hub
        ↓
docker pull
        ↓
Deploy Application
```
